nterdisciplinary collective is concerned, architecture is more than just the final, photogenic result: it is an exciting, horizon-broadening process that engages the citizens of a municipality, the inhabitants of a city neighbourhood, a company’s employees, or the students and teachers at a school as expert stakeholders. The idea behind this approach is that participation is simultaneously the best common denominator and most important foundation of lived building culture. This book offers a behind-the-scenes view of the unconventional planning office and features insights from building contractors and other experts.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aArchitektur. 4aCorporate Architecture. 4aKommunen. 4aLeerstandsnutzung. 4aNiederösterreich. 4aOberbayern. 4aPartizipationsprojekte. 4aPlanungskultur. 4aRegionalplanung. 4aSaarland. 4aStadtkernentwicklung. 4aUnternehmen. 4aWohnquartier. 4anonconform. 4aregionalpolitisch. 7aARCHITECTURE / Individual Architects & Firms / General.2bisacsh1 aCzaja, Wojciech, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeller, Barbara, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFeller, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGruber, Roland, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2022z9783110992793oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz978386859713440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978386859990940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783868599909423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783868599909/original  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHA